01:00:20.340 --> 01:00:24.120
of many novels these days?

01:00:24.120 --> 01:00:25.420
&gt;&gt; Abubakar Adam Ibrahim: Oh.

01:00:25.420 --> 01:00:26.720
[Inaudible], okay.

01:00:26.720 --> 01:00:30.560
Yeah, how the story came to me.

01:00:30.560 --> 01:00:33.400
I was sitting down, minding
my business, you know,

01:00:33.400 --> 01:00:36.130
watching Barcelona [Laughs].

01:00:36.130 --> 01:00:42.680
But then I had this vision of
this very rascally person jumping

01:00:42.680 --> 01:00:47.340
over a woman's fence and going
into her house to burglar it

01:00:47.340 --> 01:00:49.810
and then ends up meeting
the owner of the house.

01:00:49.810 --> 01:00:53.730
So I became really curious
about what the burglar

01:00:53.730 --> 01:00:55.920
and the person who's being burgled.

01:00:55.920 --> 01:00:58.450
And I said, "You know, just
follow them and see what happens."

01:00:58.450 --> 01:01:00.950
And that was how the
story came about.

01:01:00.950 --> 01:01:06.680
So I've also been really
curious about age

01:01:06.680 --> 01:01:10.830
and sexuality, especially
in Nigeria.

01:01:10.830 --> 01:01:14.170
It's very common to have a
60-year-old man marrying a girl

01:01:14.170 --> 01:01:17.200
who is 17 or 18, you
know, and nobody frowns

01:01:17.200 --> 01:01:20.220
about it or nobody frowns at it.

01:01:20.220 --> 01:01:25.120
But then if a woman who is 35
is marrying someone who is 27,

01:01:25.120 --> 01:01:27.250
you know, it becomes a problem.

01:01:27.250 --> 01:01:29.160
What do you mean, she's older?

01:01:29.160 --> 01:01:30.500
Old enough to be your mother?

01:01:30.500 --> 01:01:32.120
That is what they will tell you.

01:01:32.120 --> 01:01:38.380
You know? I remember when
I was in secondary school

01:01:38.380 --> 01:01:41.850
and I was dating this girl who
was in the same class as me.

01:01:41.850 --> 01:01:43.340
We were the same age.

01:01:43.340 --> 01:01:47.280
And I took her to see my mom.

01:01:47.280 --> 01:01:50.810
And my mom was very hospitable,
she received her well.

01:01:50.810 --> 01:01:55.740
After the girl went, my mom
said, "She's a nice girl,

01:01:55.740 --> 01:01:57.960
but she's too old for you."

01:01:57.960 --> 01:02:02.400
And I was like, "Okay.

01:02:02.400 --> 01:02:04.560
But she's my age [inaudible],
right?"

01:02:04.560 --> 01:02:09.550
So when I was 26 I dated a girl who
was 26, same age, same everything.

01:02:09.550 --> 01:02:12.430
And, again, of course, I
wanted to marry her then

01:02:12.430 --> 01:02:14.700
because I was 26, right,
not 17 or 18.

01:02:14.700 --> 01:02:22.110
And my mom said, "Oh, she's a nice
girl, but she's too old for you."

01:02:22.110 --> 01:02:24.970
[Laughs] So these perceptions
are common.

01:02:24.970 --> 01:02:29.750
In Nigeria it's common that
you should have maybe five,

01:02:29.750 --> 01:02:33.780
ten years difference between
a man and a woman marrying;

01:02:33.780 --> 01:02:37.550
but the man has to be older, right?

01:02:37.550 --> 01:02:39.960
So I was, like, if
we reverse this role,

01:02:39.960 --> 01:02:42.450
what if the woman is older
who's having this relationship

01:02:42.450 --> 01:02:46.290
with this guy who is much
younger, what happens?

01:02:46.290 --> 01:02:49.180
So that was one of the
premise I started off with.

01:02:49.180 --> 01:02:54.240
And then again, you have issues
of how would her children react,

01:02:54.240 --> 01:02:58.420
how would people around react,
how would they see these issues?

01:02:58.420 --> 01:03:01.440
And I felt it's important
because most times when we talk

01:03:01.440 --> 01:03:07.670 position:56%
about the sexuality of older women,
we -- in Nigeria we say sugar mommy.

01:03:07.670 --> 01:03:09.790
You know? And the general
perception is that well,

01:03:09.790 --> 01:03:12.080
she's going into it for the sex.

01:03:12.080 --> 01:03:15.100
And she has to pay the young
guy to agree to sleep with her.

01:03:15.100 --> 01:03:17.890
And in this scenario
that is not the case.

01:03:17.890 --> 01:03:20.270
Yes, sex was at the heart
of the relationship,

01:03:20.270 --> 01:03:22.800
but there was something much more.

01:03:22.800 --> 01:03:27.130
For Binta there was this desire to
redeem this character, you know,

01:03:27.130 --> 01:03:30.030
the character of Hausa Reza,
to make him a better person

01:03:30.030 --> 01:03:32.080
in her own, you know, fashion.

01:03:32.080 --> 01:03:36.200
So that was something that was
playing in her mind as well.

01:03:36.200 --> 01:03:39.430
So it wasn't really -- I was
trying to break this mold

01:03:39.430 --> 01:03:42.960
of older women being sugar
mommies for whatever reason.

01:03:42.960 --> 01:03:46.810
People can have relationship
for something much more profound

01:03:46.810 --> 01:03:51.860
than for, you know, just the
pleasure of it and then for sake

01:03:51.860 --> 01:03:55.020
of making some extra
income or something.

